Description: Fragment of flattened handle to sharpish turn of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp. Clay fine pale beige.
Production date: 152 BC (see N. Badoud, Le temps de Rhodes, 2015, 142.)
Curator's comments: Name Pausanias. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0192.47.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0963)
